main event: An unidentified object was sighted traveling at 600 knots at an altitude of 5000 ft over Hubbard, Ohio on May 26, 1958.
interesting points: The object was described as round and orange., It emitted a constant light with no flashing or pulsating., The direction of movement was from southeast to northwest., The observer indicated the object resembled a typical jet aircraft., The details about the sighting were largely unknown or unobserved.
